    .csv("03-30-2020.csv")

println("Record count: " + df.count)
df.printSchema()
df.show(5)

df.registerTempTable("coronareport")

paragraphs.text:
%sql
select
    Country_Region as Country,
    sum(Confirmed) as Confirmed,
    sum(Deaths) as Deaths,
    sum(Recovered) as Recovered,
    sum(Active) as Active,
    (sum(Deaths) / sum(Confirmed) * 100 ) as DeathRatioPerConfirmed,
    (sum(Deaths) / (sum(Recovered) + sum(Deaths)) * 100 ) as DeathRatioPerClosed
from coronareport
group by Country
order by 2 desc

from coronareport

import org.apache.spark.sql.types._

val dfConfirmed = spark.read
    .options(Map("inferSchema"->"true","header"->"true"))
    .csv("time_series_covid19_confirmed_global_narrow.csv")
    .withColumnRenamed("Province/State", "State")
    .withColumnRenamed("Country/Region", "Country")
    .withColumn("Date", col("Date").cast(DateType))
    .withColumn("Value", col("Value").cast(IntegerType))

val dfDeaths = spark.read
    .options(Map("inferSchema"->"true","header"->"true"))
    .csv("time_series_covid19_deaths_global_narrow.csv")
    .withColumnRenamed("Province/State", "State")
    .withColumnRenamed("Country/Region", "Country")
    .withColumn("Date", col("Date").cast(DateType))
    .withColumn("Value", col("Value").cast(IntegerType))
    
val dfRecovered = spark.read
    .options(Map("inferSchema"->"true","header"->"true"))
    .csv("time_series_covid19_recovered_global_narrow.csv")
    .withColumnRenamed("Province/State", "State")
    .withColumnRenamed("Country/Region", "Country")
    .withColumn("Date", col("Date").cast(DateType))
    .withColumn("Value", col("Value").cast(IntegerType))
    
println("Record count (confirmed): " + dfConfirmed.count)
dfConfirmed.printSchema()
dfConfirmed.show(5)

println("Record count (confirmed): " + dfDeaths.count)
dfDeaths.printSchema()
dfDeaths.show(5)

println("Record count (confirmed): " + dfRecovered.count)
dfRecovered.printSchema()
dfRecovered.show(5)

dfConfirmed.registerTempTable("confirmed_timeseries")
dfDeaths.registerTempTable("deaths_timeseries")
dfRecovered.registerTempTable("recovered_timeseries")

# Generic time series analysis

%sql
select cts.Country, cts.Date,
       cts.Value as confirmed,
       rts.Value as recovered,
       dts.Value as deaths,
       (cts.Value - (rts.Value + dts.Value)) as active
from confirmed_timeseries cts, recovered_timeseries rts, deaths_timeseries dts 
where cts.Country in ("Spain") and rts.Country in ("Spain") and dts.Country in ("Spain")
  and cts.Date = rts.Date
  and rts.Date = dts.Date
order by Date

paragraphs.title: Coronavirus time series (data load)
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.commons.io.IOUtils
import java.net.URL
import java.nio.charset.Charset
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions

val confirmedTimeseries = sc.parallelize(
    IOUtils.toString(
        new URL("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_time_series/time_series_covid19_confirmed_global.csv"),
        Charset.forName("utf8")).split("\n"))

val deathsTimeseries = sc.parallelize(
    IOUtils.toString(
        new URL("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_time_series/time_series_covid19_deaths_global.csv"),
        Charset.forName("utf8")).split("\n"))

var countryFilter = z.input("Country").toString

println("Country: " + countryFilter)
println("Raw CSV count (Confirmed): " + confirmedTimeseries.count)
println("Raw CSV count (Deaths): " + deathsTimeseries.count)

val confirmedTs = confirmedTimeseries
    .filter(_.contains(countryFilter))               // Get only a single country row
    .flatMap(s => s.split(",").drop(4).dropRight(1)) // Get all values (except for the first 4 columns (state, country, lon y lat) and the last one which is somehow failing)
    .map(s => s.toInt)                               // Convert to int
    .toDF()                                          // Convert to Dataframe
    .withColumn("id", functions.monotonically_increasing_id())  // Add an ID
    .withColumnRenamed("value", "confirmed")         // Rename the value column
        
val deathsTs = deathsTimeseries
    .filter(_.contains(countryFilter))               // Get only a single country row
    .flatMap(s => s.split(",").drop(4).dropRight(1)) // Get all values (except for the first 4 columns (state, country, lon y lat) and the last one which is somehow failing)
    .map(s => s.toInt)                               // Convert to int
    .toDF()                                          // Convert to Dataframe
    .withColumn("id", functions.monotonically_increasing_id())  // Add an ID
    .withColumnRenamed("value", "deaths")            // Rename the value column

val ts = confirmedTs
    .join(deathsTs, "id")
    .orderBy("id")

ts.show(5)

ts.registerTempTable("ts")
